Some notes and refs about a possible raster-in-db implementation

== References ==
 * [http://www.gdal.org CHIP driver for GDAL] - Contains the PGCHIP driver, recently fixed to avoid use of reserved CHIP fields. Can be used to import and export grayscale, single band, 8 and 16 bpp rasters.

 * [http://portal.opengeospatial.org/files/?artifact_id=6628 OpenGIS Grid Coverage Service Implementation Specification]
 * [http://www.gdal.org/gdal_drivertut.html GDAL Driver implementation tutorial] - for pgchip fixes or new work.
 * [http://download.oracle.com/docs/pdf/B10827_01.pdf Oracle GeoRaster] for example of a raster database API (requires authentication)
 * [http://www.oracle.com/technology/products/spatial/pdf/10gr2_collateral/spatial_twp_georaster_10gr2.pdf Oracle Database 10g, Managing Spatial Raster Data Using GeoRasterÂ—Technical White Paper (PDF)] - no authentication required

 * [http://www.varlena.com/GeneralBits/44.php Smart BLOBS on General Bits] - Contains tips on how to wrap large_objects into custom datatypes.

== PostGIS WKT Raster ==
 * [wiki:WKTRaster Pierre Racine's proposal]  - and related thread [http://postgis.refractions.net/pipermail/postgis-users/2008-December/022076.html http://postgis.refractions.net/pipermail/postgis-users/2008-December/022076.html]

== PGRaster ==
